This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with semantic edge detection, which is a fundamental task in computer vision. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel fully convolutional neural network architecture, which is a popular technique in computer vision research.

The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

Furthermore, the paper proposes a multi-task framework, which involves training the network to perform multiple tasks simultaneously. This is a common approach in the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.

Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on several benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
